From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000007 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ttyS3 <ttys3.rust@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 14:12:46 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix(unicode): commit Linux/BSD filename conversions to UTF-8

Background
==========
libunrar's WideToChar / CharToWide in unicode.cpp branch on platform:

  - Windows (_WIN_ALL): WideCharToMultiByte(CP_ACP, ...) - OS-level
    codepage, independent of any libc setlocale state. NTFS wide-native.
  - Apple (_APPLE, auto-defined via raros.hpp:18-20 on __APPLE__):
    WideToUtf / UtfToWide - pure character-arithmetic UTF-8 transforms,
    zero libc dependency.
  - Other Unix (MBFUNCTIONS): wcsrtombs / mbsrtowcs - depend on the
    process LC_CTYPE.

The MBFUNCTIONS branch is the buggy one for library use. The standalone
`unrar` CLI hides the bug because rar.cpp:8 calls setlocale(LC_ALL, "")
in main(). Library users have no equivalent hook, so a process inheriting
LC_CTYPE=C/POSIX (systemd units, minimal Docker images, SMB-side
fileserver processes, etc.) makes wcsrtombs degrade to WideToCharMap,
writing literal '_' for every non-ASCII wchar (unicode.cpp:185). CJK /
accented filenames become long runs of underscores on disk.

Empirically (Linux + LC_ALL=C, against unpatched 0.7.5), the bug is
confined to RARExtractAll(W) - the batch extract path used by
unrar-ng's `OpenArchive::extract_all` and `extract_all_with_callback`.
The per-file extract path (`pathed/linux.rs::preprocess_extract`)
constructs the full destination path in Rust and passes it through
RARProcessFile's ANSI DestName parameter, which rides a private-use-area
round-trip in CharToWideMap/WideToCharMap and is locale-immune. The
batch path lets libunrar internally derive the output filename from the
archive's wstring (real CJK codepoints), which the private-use round-trip
cannot rescue, hence the mangling.

Decision
========
This patch extends the _APPLE branch in WideToChar (line ~30) and
CharToWide (line ~95) to also fire when UNRAR_NG_FORCE_UTF8 is defined.
unrar-ng-sys's build.rs defines it when cargo feature
`linux-batch-extract-utf8` is enabled (default-on) AND the target is
non-Apple non-Windows Unix. Result: both directions of wide<->8bit
filename conversion are pure UTF-8 transforms with no libc dependency.

This is a conscious narrowing versus standalone `unrar` CLI behavior:
when CLI runs under LANG=zh_CN.GBK it emits GBK byte filenames; this
patch emits UTF-8 byte filenames regardless of LANG. The narrowing is
justified because:

  - Modern Linux filesystem convention is UTF-8 (every userspace tool,
    GUI, FS driver default, distro init system since ~2010).
  - GBK / Shift-JIS / EUC-* LANG settings have effectively disappeared
    from real-world Linux installations by 2026 (no major distro
    defaults to them; glibc 2.13+ ships C.UTF-8).
  - Calling setlocale at library load (the alternative that would
    preserve CLI parity for legacy locales) perturbs the host process's
    libc state for ALL callers to benefit a niche population that
    barely exists.
  - WideToUtf / UtfToWide are deterministic, locale-independent, and
    already the proven correct path on macOS where filesystem semantics
    are identical to modern Linux.

Callers who DO need legacy-codepage byte output can opt out by setting
`default-features = false` on `unrar-ng`. With the feature off, the
upstream MBFUNCTIONS branch (wcsrtombs / mbsrtowcs) is restored. They
can additionally enable `linux-batch-extract-setlocale` to have the
crate auto-init LC_CTYPE via OnceLock at the first batch-extract call,
matching CLI behavior without writing setlocale code themselves.

Patch scope
===========
- unicode.cpp WideToChar (~line 30):
    #elif defined(_APPLE)
  becomes
    #elif defined(_APPLE) || defined(UNRAR_NG_FORCE_UTF8)
- unicode.cpp CharToWide (~line 95): same one-line extension
- No other vendored file modified.
- _WIN_ALL branch unchanged (Windows behavior unaffected).
- _APPLE branch unchanged (macOS behavior unaffected).
- MBFUNCTIONS branch reachable when both _APPLE and UNRAR_NG_FORCE_UTF8
  are absent, i.e. with `linux-batch-extract-utf8` cargo feature off.
---
 unicode.cpp | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/unicode.cpp b/unicode.cpp
index a9d103d..f9c8fda 100644
--- a/unicode.cpp
+++ b/unicode.cpp
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@ bool WideToChar(const wchar *Src,char *Dest,size_t DestSize)
     RetCode=false;

 // wcstombs is broken in Android NDK r9.
-#elif defined(_APPLE)
+#elif defined(_APPLE) || defined(UNRAR_NG_FORCE_UTF8)
   WideToUtf(Src,Dest,DestSize);

 #elif defined(MBFUNCTIONS)
@@ -92,7 +92,7 @@ bool CharToWide(const char *Src,wchar *Dest,size_t DestSize)
     RetCode=false;

 // mbstowcs is broken in Android NDK r9.
-#elif defined(_APPLE)
+#elif defined(_APPLE) || defined(UNRAR_NG_FORCE_UTF8)
   UtfToWide(Src,Dest,DestSize);

 #elif defined(MBFUNCTIONS)
--
